2lbs fresh flunder (or you can substitute sole or cod)
4 garlice cloves
1 tomato
4 pats of butter
2 tablespoons of olive oil
1 tablespoons of dry basil
1/2 cup of dry white wine

Pre-heat oven to 350F. Wash and dry the filets and lay them flat in a baking pan. Pour in wine. Slice tomato thin and place one or 
two slices on each filet depending on size. Dab each filet with butter. Mince garlic and spread of the top of the fish. Salt and pepper 
to taste. Bake for 30 minutes.
